          "value" : "Villager elder speaking during a meeting"
        } ]
      },
      "note" : [ {
        "text" : "Be aware of how your own body language might have a different meaning in Afghanistan. Afghan gestures have more sweeping or invitational motions than American gestures. For instance, your counterpart might use all fingers and an open palm to point at something, rather than using their index finger, which might be considered rude.",
